HEADWORD: Andante
<hw>An*dan"te</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>andante</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>andare</ets> to go.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Moving moderately slow, but distinct and flowing;
quicker than larghetto, and slower than allegretto.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A movement or piece in andante
time.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Andantino</ent>⟦br⟧
